cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper proposes a model for abstractive sentence summarization, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model uses recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The selective gate network is designed to control the information flow, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the model on three datasets, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
